You are building a Blazor WebAssembly PWA for building inspectors on construction sites. The project is already scaffolded at /tmp/sv-e11e3533b0ac451081f331cd6e79a975/SiteInspector/ with a server project (SiteInspector) and client project (SiteInspector.Client).

## Requirements
- Inspectors fill out safety checklists and add notes at each site visit
- Photos attached to inspection reports
- MUST work offline (construction sites have poor/no cellular)
- Syncs to server when connectivity returns
- Mobile phones and tablets (not desktop)
- Low-latency UI — inspectors tap through checklist items quickly
- No authentication

## Architecture Decisions
- **PWA with service worker** for offline support
- **IndexedDB** (via JS interop) for local data persistence
- **Background sync** when connectivity returns
- All interactive components in `.Client` project
- Server project provides API endpoints for sync
- Mobile-first responsive CSS with large tap targets

## Implementation Plan

### 1. Shared Models (in a new SiteInspector.Shared project or just in .Client)
Put models in `SiteInspector.Client/Models/`:

```csharp
// InspectionModels.cs
namespace SiteInspector.Client.Models;

public class ConstructionSite
{
    public string Id { get; set; } = Guid.NewGuid().ToString();
    public string Name { get; set; } = "";
